\c 99
\p
\v 1 The Lord reigneth, let the people tremble: he sitteth betweene the Cherubims, let the earth be moued.
\v 2 The Lord is great in Zion, and he is high aboue all the people.
\v 3 They shall prayse thy great and fearefull Name (for it is holy)
\v 4 And the Kings power, that loueth iudgement: for thou hast prepared equitie: thou hast executed iudgement and iustice in Iaakob.
\v 5 Exalt the Lord our God, and fall downe before his footestoole: for he is holy.
\v 6 Moses and Aaron were among his Priests, and Samuel among such as call vpon his Name: these called vpon the Lord, and he heard them.
\v 7 Hee spake vnto them in the cloudie pillar: they kept his testimonies, and the Lawe that he gaue them.
\v 8 Thou heardest them, O Lord our God: thou wast a fauourable God vnto them, though thou didst take vengeance for their inuentions.
\v 9 Exalt the Lord our God, and fall downe before his holy Mountaine: for the Lord our God is holy.